Bring a #large pot{} of @water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{8%ounce}. (Skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!)

Once water is boiling, add @ramen noodles{4.5%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring, until just softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Drain and rinse noodles under cold water for at least ~{30%seconds}, then toss with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in #pot used for noodles over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites, ginger, and half the garlic. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir @water{3%cups} (6 cups for 4 servings), @hoisin sauce{2%tablespoon}, @miso sauce concentrate{2}, and @veggie pho stock concentrate{2} into #pot with aromatics. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low.

> Taste broth and season with salt if desired.

Simmer, covered, until ready to serve.

While broth simmers, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, remaining garlic, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Add @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}; stir to coat.

Divide noodles between large #soup bowls{}. Pour broth over noodles. Top each bowl with mushroom mixture and any remaining sauce from pan.

Sprinkle with scallion greens and drizzle with @sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste. Garnish with a few @crispy fried onions{1} and serve.

> Don't add all the crispy onions just yet! Add more as you eat to keep them crispy.